:43.968Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Under `./system/ee/legacy/libraries/Image_lib.php`\n\nThere are function from CodeIgniter to manipulate images. The issue is that the PHP function `exec` is used two times in two different functions: `image_process_imagemagick` and `image_process_netpbm`\n\nIn both cases the `full_src_path` and `full_dst_path` are given unescaped to the `exec` function. If an attacker can control the filename of the image to give he can inject pretty much arbitrary code. I suggest to use `escapeshellarg` on the path arguments at rows:\n-590\n-604\n-608\n-691\n\nFurthermore, note that in CodeIgniter Github repo, the function `image_process_imagemagick` that already prevents this potential injection.\nhttps://github.com/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/blob/27647c9a8b5cd5a0e1fd78123316f359fe61a672/system/libraries/Image_lib.php#L892\n","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eUnder \u003ccode\u003e./system/ee/legacy/libraries/Image_lib.php\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are function from CodeIgniter to manipulate images. The issue is that the PHP function \u003ccode\u003eexec\u003c/code\u003e is used two times in two different functions: \u003ccode\u003eimage_process_imagemagick\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eimage_process_netpbm\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn both cases the \u003ccode\u003efull_src_path\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003efull_dst_path\u003c/code\u003e are given unescaped to the \u003ccode\u003eexec\u003c/code\u003e function. If an attacker can control the filename of the image to give he can inject pretty much arbitrary code. I suggest to use \u003ccode\u003eescapeshellarg\u003c/code\u003e on the path arguments at rows:\u003cbr\u003e\n-590\u003cbr\u003e\n-604\u003cbr\u003e\n-608\u003cbr\u003e\n-691\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFurthermore, note that in CodeIgniter Github repo, the function \u003ccode\u003eimage_process_imagemagick\u003c/code\u003e that already prevents this potential injection.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca title=\"https://github.com/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/blob/27647c9a8b5cd5a0e1fd78123316f359fe61a672/system/libraries/Image_lib.php#L892\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fbcit-ci%2FCodeIgniter%2Fblob%2F27647c9a8b5cd5a0e1fd78123316f359fe61a672%2Fsystem%2Flibraries%2FImage_lib.php%23L892\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://github.com/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/blob/27647c9a8b5cd5a0e1fd78123316f359fe61a672/system/libraries/Image_lib.php#L892\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","weakness":{"id":70,"name":"Code Injection"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":null,"vote_count":3,"voters":["generaleg","eveeez","japz"],"severity":{"rating":"medium","author_type":"User"},"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":1844282,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"Thanks, @freetom! The file names should be sanitized by the time they make it to the image library so there shouldn't be any problem on the front-end, but we'll make sure they're still sanitized and escaped as you suggested for any third-parties using the library without proper sanitization/validation. This fix will be in our next release.","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eThanks, \u003ca href=\"/freetom\"\u003e@freetom\u003c/a\u003e! The file names should be sanitized by the time they make it to the image library so there shouldn\u0026#39;t be any problem on the front-end, but we\u0026#39;ll make sure they\u0026#39;re still sanitized and escaped as you suggested for any third-parties using the library without proper sanitization/validation. This fix will be in our next release.\u